cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with user association in heterogeneous networks, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of biasing and uplink/downlink decoupling techniques, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a system (i.e., the network) through user association. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the impact of user association on multimedia applications in HetNets. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper may discuss the game-theoretic aspects of user association in HetNets.
